            "sections": [
                {
                    "body": "A fire beetle's glowing glands provide light in a 10-foot radius. A dead fire beetle's luminescent glands continue to glow for 1d6 days after its death.", 
                    "name": "Luminescence", 
                    "url": "pfsrd://Bestiary/Monsters/Beetle/Fire/Special Abilities/Luminescence", 
                    "ability_types": {
                        "ability_type": "Extraordinary"
                    }, 
                    "source": "Bestiary", 
                    "type": "ability"
                }
            ]
        }, 
        {
            "body": "<p>Although nocturnal, the fire beetle lacks darkvision&mdash;it relies on its own glowing glands for illumination. Caged fire beetles are a popular source of long-lasting illumination among eccentrics and miners.</p>", 
            "source": "Bestiary", 
            "type": "section"
        }, 
        {
            "body": "<p>Other variations on the common fire beetle exist. The two most common variants are detailed below.</p>", 
            "source": "Bestiary", 
            "type": "section"
        }, 
        {
            "url": "pfsrd://Bestiary/Monsters/Beetle/Fire/Mining Beetle (CR 1_2)", 
            "type": "section", 
            "sections": [
                {
                    "body": "<p>A mining beetle is an advanced fire beetle with the advanced simple template and a burrowing speed of 20 feet.</p>", 
                    "source": "Bestiary", 
                    "type": "section"
                }
            ], 
            "name": "Mining Beetle (CR 1/2)", 
            "source": "Bestiary"
        }, 
        {
            "url": "pfsrd://Bestiary/Monsters/Beetle/Fire/Flash Beetle (CR 1_2)", 
            "type": "section", 
            "sections": [
                {
                    "body": "<p>A flash beetle is an advanced fire beetle that can create a bright flash of light once an hour. When a flash beetle does so, all creatures in a 10-foot burst must make a DC 12 Fortitude save or be dazzled for 1d3 rounds. The save DC is Constitution-based.</p>", 
                    "source": "Bestiary", 
                    "type": "section"
                }
            ], 
            "name": "Flash Beetle (CR 1/2)", 
            "source": "Bestiary"
        }
